{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a9f746f4-2603-486d-8d3a-36ca957259ae","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order in the `.fsproj` matters — files must be listed in dependency order. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but it's listed first. Let me fix the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_F6dZso2VOI2AGKpPsHOq6p","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8a1cf500ab6b4c0187a3cfb09c76f12b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8a1cf500ab6b4c0187a3cfb09c76f12b/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"e2355e89-a3da-452c-8c73-5423a12cba59","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files must be listed in dependency order in the `.fsproj` file. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), but in the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`. This means the compiler will try to compile `Services.fs` first, but it won't find the `BrokenOrder.Domain` module yet.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`, and `Program.fs` comes last (since it depends on both).","outputTokens":443,"requestId":"5BCB:1E9F:408ADBC:480965F:69F9E5DD"},"id":"6565d4fe-ff6f-4dd9-9603-3d55bce968b9","timestamp":"2026-05-05T12:43:17.742Z","parentId":"c260b0a3-0afb-4a85-b509-fca16b376990"}
